               <nationality type="Ethiopia"/>
               
                  
                
               
               <occupation type="military">leader</occupation>
               <floruit notBefore="1617" notAfter="1627">He was one of the first <persName ref="ETH1973Oromo"/> 
                  war leaders recruited in <date>1617</date> to the royal service of King
                  <persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos"/> . Bukko proved to be indispensable as general for the Emperor 
                  whose territories were endangered by regular <persName ref="ETH1973Oromo"/> raids
                  and whose <persName ref="ETH1126Amhara"/> warriors were unaccustomed to 
                  <persName ref="ETH1973Oromo"/> warfare. So he was appointed both <roleName type="title">daǧǧāzmāč</roleName>,
                  <roleName type="title">ṣaḥafe lām</roleName> of <placeName ref="LOC2488Damot">Dāmot</placeName> where his main duty was 
                  to repel <persName ref="ETH1973Oromo"/> raids into the province under his government. Bukko rather being 
                  detached from the burning conflict between  Catholic converts and Orthodox Christians in the country, 
                  was often sent by <persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos"/> to render military assistance to his staunch 
                  Catholic half brother <persName ref="PRS8681SeelaK"/>,
                  the governor of <placeName ref="LOC3549Gojjam"/> much hated by the Orthodox Christians. </floruit>
               <death when="1627">He was killed on 
                  <date>25-09-1627</date>in an encounter with a raiding <persName ref="ETH1973Oromo"/> tribe. 
               </death>
